  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\n* Now, there are `contract_bytecode` , `contract_address` and `function_signature`\r\n* I just used `new_transaction` to create a `tx` and call `chain.get_transaction_result(tx, chain.get_canonical_head())` to get the result.\r\n\r\n**Code:**\r\n```\r\ntx = new_transaction(\r\n    chain.get_vm(),\r\n    SENDER,\r\n    contract_address,\r\n    data = function_signature,\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\n* `contract_bytecode` is used as a parameter in `genesis_state` which used to create the chain.\r\n```\r\ndef genesis_state(base_genesis_state, simple_contract_address):\r\n        return assoc(\r\n            base_genesis_state,\r\n            simple_contract_address,\r\n            {\r\n                'balance': 0,\r\n                'nonce': 0,\r\n                'code': decode_hex(`contract_bytecode`),\r\n                'storage': {},\r\n        },\r\n    )\r\n```\r\n\r\n* But it only executed the initial part, then return, opcode sequence like\r\n```\r\n[ PUSH1, PUSH1, MSTORE, PUSH2, DUP1, PUSH2, PUSH1, CODECOPY, PUSH1, RETURN ]\r\n```\r\n* **Not call the specific function corresponding to the `function_signature` !**\r\n\r\nI'll appreciate it very much if you could help me deal with this problem!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
